-- MOVES-SocGen unit strengthens natural resources & energy financing team
-- 
-- Thu Sep 18, 2014 06:14AM EDT
-- None



Sept 18 (Reuters) - Societe Generale Corporate & Investment Banking boosted its natural resources and energy financing team, naming senior executives in its Paris and Hong Kong offices.

The unit of Societe Generale <SOGN.PA>, France's third-largest bank by assets, named Stephanie Clement de Givry global head of metals & mining finance. Givry replaces Chin-Eav Eap, who will take up the newly created position of regional head of metals & mining finance for Asia Pacific in Hong Kong. Givry, who will be based in Paris, was previously head of energy and metals & mining finance teams in Asia Pacific. The company appointed Daniel Mallo the new head of the energy and metals & mining finance teams in Asia Pacific. Mallo will also share the role of co-head of natural resources & energy financing group for Asia Pacific.